The Register is a small folio volume, not in its original binding, consisting of 196 leaves of vellum, which have all been numbered and in their present posi- tion, as early as the middle os the fifteenth century.

From folio 20 to solio 152 inclusive, the deeds are engrossed sometimes in single, sometimes in double columns, by several different hands, but, with very few exception& in writing of the thirteenth century.8

From the 152d leaf to the 169th, the hand-writing is of the 14th century3 and the remainder of the volume is in a later hand.
